looking at imbued ogre war armor, which is a bit better in ac (the BP is 7 ac better).  I have about 10k possible and am looking for a full set minus the hands.  I've read through other posts on similar questions, but my main concern is how good does the ac have to be to equal or beat the str/sta of crusty?  For instance, will the imbued ogre armor be about the same all things considered?  Would it be worth buying acrylia, or perhaps saving up and getting each piece of engraved royal velium?  Thanks in advance for the advice. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhagulim>rhagulim</A> at: 1/12/03 4:45:07 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=neksnappa>Neksnappa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/12/03 12:19:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4839.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Upgrade After Crusty?</span><hr size=1> I'm in the same boat as you, i still have crusty arms/legs/boots that im ready to upgrade. My solution is going to be thurg armor, as i already have the faction necessary for the quests, and the plat for the gems. Are you in a guild that raids kael often? Or you could go for the kael armor, or the SS armor. Some good upgrades for cheap would be Barbed ringmail (30ac 9str 50hp ~ 2k) and pieces of crystal chitin. With the bazaar, there are tons of items for sale for cheap that are upgrades to crusty. If you have luclin, just use the bazaar and search by slot for every piece you need. With 10k, you could spend maybe 1k per slot on average and get a bunch of new armor that will be all you need for a while. <br>
